data.name: Ribbon.Items.Inflate.Tip
data.value: Inflates the selected element(s) by 10 pixels. The width and height is increased by 10 pixels and the elements are moved so that the center remains in the same place.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.Deflate.Tip
data.value: Deflates the selected element(s) by 10 pixels. The width and height is decreased by 10 pixels and the elements are moved so that the center remains in the same place.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.Wider.Tip
data.value: Enlarges the width of the selected element(s) by 10 pixels. The elements are moved so that the center remains in the same place.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.Narrower.Tip
data.value: Reduces the width of the selected element(s) by 10 pixels. The elements are moved so that the center remains in the same place.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.Higher.Tip
data.value: Enlarges the height of the selected element(s) by 10 pixels. The elements are moved so that the center remains in the same place.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.Lower.Tip
data.value: Reduces the height of the selected element(s) by 10 pixels. The elements are moved so that the center remains in the same place.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.MoveLeft.Tip
data.value: Moves the selected element(s) to the left by 10 pixels.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.MoveRight.Tip
data.value: Moves the selected element(s) to the right by 10 pixels.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.MoveUp.Tip
data.value: Moves the selected element(s) up by 10 pixels.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.MoveDown.Tip
data.value: Moves the selected element(s) down by 10 pixels.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.MoveStartToZero.Tip
data.value: Moves all elements of the active diagram to make the diagram bounds starting at coordinates x=0, y=0.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.ResetRotation.Tip
data.value: Resets rotation of the selected element(s) to the default unrotated state.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.GenerateHierarchyDiagram.Tip
data.value: Opens a dialog where you can define details of generated hierarchical diagram. You can choose a type of diagram, a type of connectors, a type of element (which will be used for boxes in the hierarchy) and direction of relationships (from child to parent/from parent to child). The hierarchy is defined as a simple indented text.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.GenerateUmlDiagram.Tip
data.value: Generates a new UML diagram from a text. A correct UML text notation must be used to generate a new diagram.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.GenerateProjectHierarchy.Tip
data.value: Generates a package diagram with a hierarchy of folders in the current project. A project folder is represented by UML Package and folder nesting is shown using a containment relationship.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.ProjectProperties.Tip
data.value: Opens Project Properties window, where you can set the name, authors and description of the current project.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.FolderProperties.Tip
data.value: Shows the Folder Properties dialog for the active folder. This dialog allows you to set the name of the folder, the custom namespace (otherwise the default name for namespace is used) and documentation.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.ProjectDocumentation.Tip
data.value: Opens a window with a list of all documents in the current project.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.Glossary.Tip
data.value: Opens Glossary window, which allows you to add, edit and delete the glossary terms.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.Tasks.Tip
data.value: Opens Task Management window, where you can manage the tasks associated with the current project.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.Persons.Tip
data.value: Opens Persons window, where you can edit the list of persons associated with the current project.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.DuplicateDiagram.Tip
data.value: Show Duplicate Diagram dialog, which allows you to specify the kind of the copy (independent/shared model), name prefixes and suffixes and also to create relationship diagram between original and the new duplicated diagram.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.SplitDiagram.Tip
data.value: Splits the active diagram to multiple diagrams so that a new diagram will be created for each separate graph.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.AddAllModelRelationshipsToDiagram.Tip
data.value: Adds all mising relationships defined in the model to the active diagram.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.ConvertDiagram.Tip
data.value: Converts the active diagram and its elements to another kind.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.DiagramProperties.Tip
data.value: Opens the Diagram Properties dialog, which allows you to set the name, custom namespace, authors, version, description and documentation of the current active diagram. Diagram Properties dialog contains also the read-only information about creation date and date of last change.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.ShowPartsInDiagram.Tip
data.value: Sets which parts (e.g. custom IDs, parent name, stereotypes, etc.) should be displayed and which hidden. Individual settings of elements can override this default setting. Some part settings don't need to be applied on some types of elements.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.ExportDiagram.Tip
data.value: Exports the active diagram to various image formats.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.CopyDiagram.Tip
data.value: Copies the active diagram to the clipboard.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.AddLayer.Tip
data.value: Adds a new layer in the active diagram.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.Layers.Tip
data.value: Shows a list of layers of the active diagram. It allows you to activate another layer.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.HideLayer.Tip
data.value: Hides the active layer in the active diagram.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.DeleteLayer.Tip
data.value: Deletes the active layer in the active diagram.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.MergeLayers.Tip
data.value: Merges all layers in the active diagram to a single layer.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.ShowAllLayers.Tip
data.value: Makes visible all layers in the active diagram .

data.name: Ribbon.Items.CreateNewFilter.Tip
data.value: Shows a dialog which allows you to create and apply a new filter with custom rules to the active diagram.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.Filters.Tip

data.name: Ribbon.Items.ShowAllElements.Tip
data.value: Removes the filter. All elements will be shown.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.HideComments.Tip
data.value: Applies the filter to the active diagram, which hides all comments and their connector lines.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.HideCollaborations.Tip

data.name: Ribbon.Items.Comparison.Tip
data.value: Shows Comparison Choice dialog, which allows to choose two projects for comparison and the comparison method.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.TrackChanges.Tip
data.value: Turns on/off change tracking in the current project. If this item is checked, the change tracking is active.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.HighlightChanges.Tip
data.value: Turns on/off change highlighting. If the change tracking is active, all changes will be highlighted in diagrams. New elements are highlighted with a green outline. Removed elements are highlighted with a red outline. Modified elements are highlighted with a yellow outline.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.ShowChanges.Tip
data.value: Shows Tracked Changes window which allows you to view changes of any item in the current project.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.AcceptChanges.Tip
data.value: Accepts changes on selected elements. All changes are definitively applied to elements and their change state is switched to unchanged.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.RejectChanges.Tip
data.value: Rejects changes on selected elements. All changes are reverted and their change state is switched to unchanged.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.AcceptAllChanges.Tip
data.value: Accepts all changes in the project. All changes are definitively applied to elements and their change state is switched to unchanged.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.RejectAllChanges.Tip
data.value: Rejects all changes in the project. All changes are reverted and their change state is switched to unchanged.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.RenumberElementIds.Tip
data.value: Opens the dialog, which provides an easy and fast way to order elements and renumber their IDs.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.GenerateIndexesForForeignKeys.Tip
data.value: Generates an index for each foreign key of each entity in entity relationship diagram.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.NetFrameworkReverseEngineering.Tip

data.name: Ribbon.Items.DatabaseReverseEngineering.Tip

data.name: Ribbon.Items.SourceCodeReverseEngineering.Tip
data.value: Shows the dialog for reverse engineering from source code. It allows you to import elements from an existing source code.

data.value: Replaces the model of a selected element. It shows the dialog window, which contains the list of all elements. You can choose one of these elements for replacement. The model of the element selected in the diagram will be replaced with the model of the element chosen in the dialog window. After confirming the action, these two elements will act as one (they share their model).

data.name: Ribbon.Items.PasteAsIndependentCopy.Tip
data.value: Inserts the elements from the clipboard to the current diagram as indepedent copies which do not share their model with the original copied elements.

data.name: Ribbon.Items.PasteAsNewInstance.Tip
data.value: Inserts the elements from the clipboard to the current diagram as new instances of copied elements - they will share the model with the original copied elements. The changes on these copies will be automatically reflected on original elements.
